article.headline: Norfolk St. 69, Winston-Salem 51
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- Corey Lyons scored 23 points, leading four Norfolk State players in double figures in a 69-51 win over Winston-Salem on Monday night. Michael Deloach scored 14 points and Kyle O'Quinn added 10 for the Spartans (7-11), who shot 48.1 percent from the field (26 of 54) en route to victory. Brandon Monroe notched a double-double, scoring 10 points and grabbing 17 rebounds. Jamal Durham led the Rams (4-14) with 16 points and Brian Fisher added 12. The Rams shot just 35.7 percent from the field (20 of 56) in the loss. The Spartans jumped out to a 13-2 and never trailed in the game, taking a commanding 10 point lead at halftime. Norfolk State's defense held the Rams to just four points during the game's final 6 minutes.
